      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Report_GetReportPersonalizationParameterValue",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve personalized report parameters for a specific distribution report and job. It dynamically constructs and executes a SQL query to fetch distinct contact addresses and associated parameters from a specified source table, based on the email address mapping and distribution profile IDs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure involves dynamic SQL execution, multiple table joins, and temporary table usage, which adds to its complexity. The use of dynamic SQL requires careful handling to avoid SQL injection risks and ensure correct query construction."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
